# ASPIS brain — local hygiene for the brain itself (paths are relative to .aspis/).
# These are generated indexes and local caches, regenerated on demand by
# .aspis/scripts/ — derived artifacts (constitution rule 8), so they are not tracked.
# Durable context (DECISIONS, ARCHITECTURE, ROADMAP, rules, features) stays tracked.
index/FILE_REGISTRY.yaml
index/CODE_MAP.md
index/test-ledger.json
context/CURRENT_STATE.md
context/RECENT_CHANGES.md
config/.runtime-inventory.json
config/reference/.runtime-inventory.json
config/reference/.last-sync.json
traces/
state/
# Export runtime state — the deployed-file snapshot + audit log, rewritten on
# every `aspis export`; derived + per-machine, so not tracked (rule 8).
current/export-snapshot.json
current/export-log.jsonl
# Per-user / per-machine model assignments, generated by `aspis models --sync` from each
# machine's detected runtimes. Each contributor keeps their own; the committed default is
# the tier map in config/models.yaml.
config/agent-models.yaml
*.db
__pycache__/
